This is 42. @hotelbelair @wolfgangpuck

The alternative to aging is dying. I turn 42 on Monday. None of this life has been easy. Sometimes, it feels like I’m just trying to keep my head above water. But there are beautiful moments. Beautiful people. And I work every damn day to be better today than I was yesterday. And those are the best gifts of all. I’m grateful to be here. No matter how hard life gets, look for the beauty. For the beautiful moments. For the beautiful people who love, support, and uplift you. Look for KINDNESS. The gifts are all around us. Even when it’s not our birthday. ♥️😘 Thank you @jasonkirk22 for creating an intentionally beautiful, flawed, and raw life with me. Thank you @hotelbelair for the memories - tonight and always. ♥️

Happy National Son’s Day to my one and only - not only son - but only child! To the boy who has taught me more about myself than I will ever teach him. To the boy who helped me, finally, after over 30 years, find MY voice so that I can be HIS until he uses his own. To the boy whose struggles have torn me to pieces and put me back together again - but not into the person I was before. A better person. A bigger person. A person who isn’t afraid of confrontation and struggle and conflict - when those things are used to fight for his happiness. MY happiness too. To the boy who works harder every single day than most adults I know. Who has a better work ethic than most adults I know. Who has taught me not to take NO for an answer and give zero fucks about what anyone else thinks. To the boy who has taught me that the only people whose opinion matters are his and mine. Who has taught me to love and fight for myself as much as I love him. Nico - you are the greatest gift to this world. You are an AMAZING, KIND (“the nicest boy in second grade” as one of your own classmates has said), funny, smart, determined, stubborn, FLAWED human. I was always terrified of flaws. I always worked so hard to make things shiny and perfect. But you SHINE despite and in spite of it all. And it’s allowed me to do exactly the same. Because flaws are real. And they make for a real and fulfilling life. I am so proud to be your Mommy. You forced me to become who I was always meant to be. And I will be here - by your side, as much or little as YOU decide - to help you become exactly who YOU are meant to be. I love you with all that I have and all that I am. Thank you. #HappyNationalSonDay 💙

Lunch Date with @jasonkirk22 - exactly 15 years ago TODAY we were married on this day! 15 years later all we can manage on this day is going out to lunch because we are deep into baseball championships practices and games. Which is pretty much where I thought - hoped - we would be at this point. So here we are, enjoying white wine, whole grilled branzino, Malibu, and some adults only time before it’s back to reality and school pickups. Happy 15, Jason. Here’s to another 15. I will be 57 and you will be 62. Nico will be 24. Let’s see what we’re doing on that day, 15 years from now.

Last Day of Second Grade!

My job as Class Coordinator has officially come to an end and we officially have a Third Grader in the house!

Nico, you worked so hard this year. You owned your struggles, brought awareness about ADHD and Dyslexia to your classmates, advocated for yourself, worked with your educational therapist outside of school hours, on top of the homework everyone else had, and YOU DID IT!! You thrived because of who YOU are and you should be so proud of yourself. You’re going to do whatever you want in this life, Nico, because you’re already doing it. You haven’t let anything stop you from doing exactly what you want and if you’ve figured how to do that now, it will only get easier from here, my love.

Keep doing and being you because you’re already changing the world! Love you to infinity and beyond.

Another homemade weeknight dinner hack thanks to @blueapron. I changed this recipe up by using Mafalda pasta (instead of cavatappi) and always remember when cooking with prosciutto to go low and slow. Cook over low-medium heat in a stainless steel pan and let it smoke. Turn on those air vents! The result are crispy, crunchy and salty prosciutto pieces - if you don’t cook it this way, you end up with rubbery and greasy charcuterie and honestly, there’s nothing worse than that. The sauce is super simple; butter, Creme Fraiche, lemon juice and zest, white wine and liquid gold (pasta water). And I always double the garlic in any recipe. This was on the table in 20 minutes and after a full day on Mommy Duty, I couldn’t be more grateful. #BlueApron #CharcuterieChic #homemade #cooking #dinner #dinnerideas #pasta #pastalover #letseat #eeeeeats #laesats #recipe

Happy 9th Birthday, Nico! These past 9 years have been as equally beautiful and exhilarating as they’ve been challenging - and sometimes even seemingly impossible. It has been inspiring to watch you grow, work harder than almost anyone else I know, and find the things in life that light your soul on fire. The two biggest being baseball and your friends. You are a passionate athlete and a passionate friend. You are fiercely loved by those around you because YOU love fiercely - and that has been the most amazing thing to watch. You never hang up FaceTime with a friend or end a play date without saying, “I love you!” You love openly and freely - your family, your dog, your friends, your school. Being 8 was your best year yet and we can’t wait to see what you do with 9. You are unstoppable because you’re willing to work harder than anyone else and you do it with heart. Keep being YOU and showing the world how to get exactly what you want while being kind and full of love. And thank you for teaching us more than we will ever teach you. We can’t wait to see what’s next. 💙💙💙

First day of 3rd grade! #BacktoSchool 🍎 ✏️ 📚

First day of 3rd grade! 🍎 ✏️ 📚

Lots of nerves here today but Nico we are so proud of your bravery and we know it’s going to be another year of hard work, learning, and most of all, GROWTH! You can do hard things! 

And always remember that no matter what, we love you so much! ♥️ Now; go do your best - and forget the rest! #neurodivergent #BackToSchool #neurodiversityadvocate #ADHD #ADHDAwareness #Dyslexia #DyslexicThinker #WeCanDoHardThings #learningdifferences #learningdisabilities #thirdgrade

Not all first days of school are created equal.

When your child struggles with ADHD, Dyslexia, and a NonVerbal Learning Difference, the first day of school can be…nerve-wracking. 

This was the first school year that Nico had serious nerves on the first day. But school is getting harder. The work is getting harder. Keeping up feels harder. 

But he worked 3 days a week over the summer with his educational therapist to prepare. 

He was ready. He just needed to BELIEVE that he was ready. And when I picked him up today, he said, “Best first day EVER! I LOVE third grade, mom!! I can’t wait for tomorrow!!”

So we got these festive balloons and will be ordering in sushi tonight (crab rolls are his fave) to celebrate. Celebrate his hard work. His spirit. His belief in himself. 

Because the only limits in life are the limits we put on ourselves. Cheers to all the neurodivergent students tackling another school year with Grace, an impenetrable work ethic, and the continued work of learning to believe in themselves and their ability to do whatever they want in the world. 

#ADHD #dyslexia #learningdisabilities #neurodiversityawareness #neurodivergent #neurodiversityadvocate #backtoschool #thirdgrade

Happy #NationalSonDay to my one and only. Not only my only son, but my only child. Nico, you have already accomplished more in your 9 years of life than a lot of people do in a lifetime. You are inspiring the world - and most of all, your school - because of who you are. You are turning what some people think of as weaknesses into your Super Powers. You are teaching your classmates empathy by being vulnerable, honest, and brave all at the same time which makes you one of the strongest people I know. You are teaching them to love themselves - faults and all - because of how you love yourself and you inspire me every day to walk alongside you on this journey and show the world that being different - is not bad. It’s just different. Our society is set up to believe different is bad, and you have already shown so many that different is beautiful. Different is creative. Different is innovative. Different is powerful. 

Different changes the world. 

I am so proud to call you my son and can’t wait to continue to watch you grow and make an impact on the people and world around you. 

I love you. ♥️

Holiday Cheese and Charcuterie Platter #CharcuterieChic I don’t like to add inedible items (like glass ornaments) or generic Christmas Cookies to make my boards/tables/platters holiday themed. #CharcuterieChic is about nuance and creativity. About the less in your face obvious. Luxury is in the details. Luxury is never crammed in your face with generic (ie boring) details. Do YOU. 

Your unique stamp will go so much farther than trying to copy or imitate anyone else. Because imitation is not the sincerest form of flattery. Imitation is the sincerest form of unoriginality. Be YOU. Be original. Shine YOUR LIGHT. Whatever that means to you. 

You are special and precious and worthy regardless of what I’m doing in my home. Or the latest TikTok influencer is doing in theirs. You are an individual, you will leave your mark on the world and that’s all that matters, not what anyone else is doing.

Thank you, 2023.
Can’t wait to see what more joys 2024 brings…

Five Cheese Ravioli in a Truffle Mushroom Garlic Cream Sauce with Spinach and Pancetta. Make sure to render ALL the fat off the pancetta so it gets nice and crispy and starts to smoke in the pan. Then drain on a paper towel while you add the mushrooms and shallots straight into the smoking pan of pancetta fat. This will give the sauce a multi-layered depth of flavor that tastes like a professional Chef made it.
